<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>What are your thoughts on allowing people to downvote posts (akin to how comments can be downvoted)?</font></span><p><font size=1><u><a href="reply?id=3497227&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%57%36%4a%67%72%54%34%55%43%6b">reply</a></u></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=80></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3497293 href="vote?for=3497293&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%57%36%4a%67%72%54%34%55%43%6b"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3497293></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=cleverjake">cleverjake</a> 12 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3497293">link</a></span></div><br>
<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>I believe that is what the flag button is for. Down vote button on a story could lead to people downvoting something they don't like because it is the opposite of upvoting. Flag is more of a "this is an inappropriate story" word.</font></span><p><font size=1><u><a href="reply?id=3497293&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%57%36%4a%67%72%54%34%55%43%6b">reply</a></u></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=120></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3497334 href="vote?for=3497334&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%57%36%4a%67%72%54%34%55%43%6b"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3497334></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=VMG">VMG</a> 12 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3497334">link</a></span></div><br>
