<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>Paul - Why not create a "comment karma threshold" to remove the incentive for new users to blindly submit stories?<p>For instance, users won't get karma points for stories they submit until they reach some threshold for karma from their comments. This would be beneficial in a number of ways:<p><pre><code>  * encourage better comments from new users
  * prevent downvote capability for new users that only submit a lot of stories
  * fewer low-quality stories will be submitted</code></pre></font></span><p><font size=1><u><a href="reply?id=3498195&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%57%36%4a%67%72%54%34%55%43%6b">reply</a></u></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=80></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3498316 href="vote?for=3498316&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%57%36%4a%67%72%54%34%55%43%6b"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3498316></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=chc">chc</a> 11 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3498316">link</a></span></div><br>
